	<sect1 id="introduction">
		<title>Introduction</title>
		<para>&app; is a GNOME2 frontend for
		<ulink url="http://www.gnupg.org" type="http">Gnu Privacy Guard</ulink>.
		&app; is designed to be an easy to use &key; management tool,
		while providing basic <glossterm>encryption</glossterm> tools.
		&app; provides to following features:</para>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="generate"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="import"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="export"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="text-editor"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="file-manager"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="key-properties"/></para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><xref linkend="signatures"/></para></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		<note>Most &key; management features can be found in the <xref linkend="key-properties"/>.</note>
	</sect1>
	<sect1 id="getting-started">
		<title>Getting Started</title>
		<sect2 id="start">
			<title>To Start &app;</title>
			<para>You can start &app; in the following ways:</para>
			<variablelist>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><guimenu>Applications</guimenu> menu</term>
					<listitem>
						<para>Choose
						<menuchoice>
							<guimenu>Other</guimenu>
							<guimenuitem>GPG Keys Manager</guimenuitem>
						</menuchoice>.</para>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>Command Line</term>
					<listitem>
						<para>Type <command>seahorse</command>.</para>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
			</variablelist>
		</sect2>
